      "to_id": "cec50b17:25",
      "content": "Your orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-critic-improvements`. Commit your changes there. Do not push.\n\nMake two changes to the Synapse codebase:\n\n**Change 1 — Force task_id to number|null in send_message MCP schema**\n\nFile: `src/mcp-server.ts`\n\nThe `send_message` tool currently has no `task_id` field. Add a `task_id` parameter to its `inputSchema.properties` that must be a number or null (use JSON Schema `oneOf: [{type: \"number\"}, {type: \"null\"}]`). This forces the LLM to explicitly declare which task a message is associated with.\n\nAlso add the handler logic: in the `if (name === 'send_message')` block (around line 412), read `task_id` from args (typed as `number | null | undefined`) and if provided, pass it through to `sendMessage`. Check if `sendMessage` in `src/db.ts` already accepts a task_id parameter; if not, add it (it's a nullable column in the messages table or needs to be added).\n\nFirst check what columns `messages` table has (`src/db.ts` around line 30) to see if `task_id` already exists. If not, add it as a migration.\n\n**Change 2 — Extract all messages for test cases (not just 3 linked ones)**\n\nFile: `src/eval/extract.ts`\n\nCurrently `extractCases` only fetches the 3 linked messages (source/trigger/result by ID). Change it to fetch ALL messages exchanged during the task window by querying:\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM messages\nWHERE timestamp >= task.started_at\n  AND timestamp <= COALESCE(task.finished_at, 9999999999999)\n  AND (from_id = task.agent_id OR to_id = task.agent_id)\nORDER BY timestamp\n```\n\n(Check the actual `messages` table schema in `src/db.ts` around line 30 to confirm column names — it may use `from_id`/`to_id` or similar.)\n\nKeep the 3 linked IDs in the case JSON for traceability scoring, but expand `messages` to the full window query.\n\nBuild with `npm run build` and verify it compiles clean before committing.",
